{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χρον-ίζω</b>, <br /> (χρόνος): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>spend time,</b> περὶ Αἴγυπτον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.61. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>last, continue,</b> τὸ μὲν καλῶς ἔχον ὅπως χρονίζον εὖ μενεῖ βουλευτέον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 847; ἐν τῇ ὑστέρᾳ 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 523a23 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χρονίζωσι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 537a7; οὐ χ. τὸ ἀλγοῦν συνεχῶς ἐν τῇ σαρκί 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Sententiae” 4, compare 4th c.BC: Diogenes Cynicus Philosophus Oen.58. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> χ. δρῶν <b>persevere</b> in doing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 255b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> <b>take time, tarry, linger,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1356, “Ch.” 64 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.49, 8.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κεχρονικότες, opposed to ὑπόγυιοι τῇ ὀργῇ ὄντες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1380b5; κεχρονικὼς ἐν Ῥώμῃ 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 33.16.6; χρονίσαι κατὰ τὸ βαλανεῖον 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.417; ἡ ναῦς καὶ τὸν χρόνον τοῦτον ὃν ἐπιστέλλω σοι χρονίζει 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιστολαί” 14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>delay</b> to do, χ. καταβῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.32.1 (also χ. τοῦ ποιῆσαί τιLXX.Gen.34.19), NT.Luke.12.45. \">LXX+NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.5</b></Level3> of ailments, <b>to be</b> or <b>become chronic,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 3.28. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.6</b></Level3> of wine, <b>to be</b> or <b>become old, to have age,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 1.33a. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be prolonged</b> or <b>delayed,</b> τῶνδε πίστις οὐκ ὄκνῳ χρονίζεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 54, compare “Ch.” 957 (Lyric poetry); πολέμου χρονισθέντος 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 3.27; [τὴν εὔνοιαν] χρονιζομένην.. φιλίαν γενέσθαι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1167a11; χ. ἐν τῷ σώματι \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>continue,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pr.” 907b22; τὰ κεχρονισμένα νοσήματα 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 18(2).31. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>grow up,</b> χρονισθεὶς δ᾽ ἀπέδειξεν ἔθος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 727 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>to be located in time, made temporal,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Simplicius Philosophus “in Aristotelis Physica commentaria - Comm. in Arist. Graeca” 716.11, 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 405. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5549","accentedUnicode":"χρονίζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3118","matchingForm":"μακροχρόνιος","stepTransliteration":"makrochronios","gloss":"long-lived","_zh_tw_Gloss":"長壽","_es_Gloss":"de larga vida","_zh_Gloss":"长寿"},{"strongNumber":"G5550","matchingForm":"χρόνος","stepTransliteration":"chronos","gloss":"time","_zh_tw_Gloss":"時候, 時, 時日","_es_Gloss":"tiempo","_zh_Gloss":"时候, 时, 时日"},{"strongNumber":"G5551","matchingForm":"χρονοτριβέω","stepTransliteration":"chronotribeō","gloss":"to spend time","_zh_tw_Gloss":"耽延","_es_Gloss":"pasar tiempo","_zh_Gloss":"耽延"}],"shortDef":"to delay","mediumDef":"to delay <br /><b>to spend time; to linger, take a long time, delay; be long,</b> <ref='Mat.24.48; 25:5'>Mt. 24:48; 25:5</ref>; <ref='Luk.1.21; 12:45'>Lk. 1:21; 12:45</ref>; <ref='Heb.10.37'>Heb. 10:37</ref>*","stepGloss":"to delay","stepTransliteration":"chronizō","count":5,"_es_Definition":"retrasarse, demorarse en llegar ; quedarse un buen rato (LUC.1:21)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 繼續留下 (路 1:21)<br>2) 活動或是某種狀態超出預期延宕<br> 1a) 花時間, 徘徊, 不克前來, 長時間離開 (太 24:48; 來 10:37)<br> 1b) 拖延, 耽擱, 延遲 (太 24:48; 路 12:45)","_zh_Definition":"1) 继续留下 (路 1:21)<br>2) 活动或是某种状态超出预期延宕<br> 1a) 花时间, 徘徊, 不克前来, 长时间离开 (太 24:48; 来 10:37)<br> 1b) 拖延, 耽搁, 延迟 (太 24:48; 路 12:45)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"trì trễ; chậm trễ.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"遲延, 拖延","_es_Gloss":"demorarse","_zh_Gloss":"迟延, 拖延"}]}